%S A396297 1,4,12,28,56,104,176,288
%N A396297 Construct a planar grid by drawing a square of side 1, and then at each corner, place the midpoint of a square of side 1/sqrt(2), rotated from the first by 45 degs. From each of these four squares continue placing new squares in the same way, each time rescaled by a factor of 1/sqrt(2), as long as they don't overlap any earlier squares. Sequence gives number of squares added at the n-th stage.
%C A396297 Zach Hanks remarks that the illustration was generated by computer, but the terms of the sequence were found by hand-counting the cells in the illustration, and should be checked. He also remarks that the structure of this grid is reminiscent of the toothpick structures discussed in A139250 and related sequences.
%D A396297 Zach Hanks, Email to N. J. A. Sloane, May 22 2026.
%H A396297 Zach Hanks, <a href="/A396297/a396297.jpg">Illustration of the initial stages of the grid</a>
%Y A396297 Cf. A139250, A220500.
%K A396297 nonn,more,new
